{
  "stem": "15962.2",
  "chunk_idx": 7,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 6.7,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "And people panicked at first, because there was not enough room to even sit down.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "So it took some organizing of putting the luggage out of the way so people could at least sit down either on luggage or on the floor.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "And the worst was that other than the bucket, there were no sanitary facilities.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "Everybody did bring some food for the trip.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "But it was a most uncomfortable and scary trip in almost complete darkness, especially since we did not know where we are going or how long the trip will be.",
      "word_count": 30
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "I don't know what the rules were.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "But we did have clothing and some food with us and my most valuable possessions that were my notebooks and especially a diary that I kept in the ghetto of the daily life.",
      "word_count": 33
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "That was the beginning of noting down what generally happened or specific things that I found important to myself.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "The arrival at-- in Auschwitz [PAUSES FOR 4 SECONDS] at the ramp, of course, is well-known and well-documented and described by everybody who, who was in the same situation.",
      "word_count": 29
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Well, we were-- this, this, they seemed to have timed the arrival for those trains to happen at night.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "This was in the middle of the beginning of winter, December 18th.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And dogs, prisoners in, in-- clad in pajamas-- and the German SS chased us out of the car and shouted swear words and with clubs formed rows and marched us away from the, from the tracks into trucks and then took us to one of the camps in Birkenau.",
      "word_count": 49
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "We had to leave everything behind.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "We were not allowed to take any luggage, any hand luggage with us.",
      "word_count": 13
    }
  ],
